# Resource Access URLs

The Autotask REST API provides standardised resource paths for accessing all entities. These URLs follow a consistent pattern and support various HTTP methods for different operations.

## Base URL Structure
All resource paths begin with:
```
/atservicesrest/v1.0/
```

## Standard Resource Endpoints

| HTTP Method | Endpoint Pattern | Purpose |
|------------|-----------------|----------|
| GET | `/EntityName/entityInformation` | Retrieve entity metadata |
| GET | `/EntityName/entityInformation/fields` | Get field definitions |
| GET | `/EntityName/entityInformation/userDefinedFields` | Get custom field definitions |
| GET | `/EntityName/{id}` | Retrieve specific resource |
| GET | `/EntityName/query` | Query resources |
| GET | `/EntityName/query/count` | Get query result count |
| POST | `/EntityName/query` | Complex resource queries |
| POST | `/EntityName/query/count` | Complex query counts |
| PUT | `/EntityName/` | Create/Update resources |
| PATCH | `/EntityName/` | Partial resource updates |
| DELETE | `/EntityName/{id}` | Delete specific resource |

## Usage Notes

1. Replace `EntityName` with the actual resource name from the API documentation
2. All endpoints are case-sensitive
3. IDs in URLs must be valid resource identifiers
4. Query endpoints support pagination and filtering
5. Entity information endpoints provide metadata for integration development

